article.description: Devonnte Holland recorded 10 points and 12 rebounds and Radford defeated High Point 72-54 on Wednesday night.
article.headline: Holland carries Radford over High Point 72-54
article.linkText: Holland carries Radford over High Point 72-54
article.story: HIGH POINT, N.C. -- Devonnte Holland recorded 10 points and 12 rebounds and Radford defeated High Point 72-54 on Wednesday night. The victory assures Radford (20-9, 12-3 Big South Conference) of at least a tie for the regular-season championship. The Highlanders play at second-place Campbell (11-4) on Saturday. Ed Polite Jr. had 16 points and seven rebounds for Radford. Carlik Jones added eight assists. Jahaad Proctor had 22 points, eight rebounds and six assists for the Panthers (15-14, 8-7). Ricky Madison added 11 points. Jordan Whitehead had 10 rebounds. The Highlanders improved to 2-0 against the Panthers this season. Radford defeated High Point 69-66 on Feb. 9. High Point finishes out the regular season against UNC-Asheville on the road on Saturday. --- For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP-Top25 --- This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
